remarks: A nonempty, bounded-above set of reals has a supremum.  Stronger version of completeness axiom (it has a slightly weaker antecedent). (Contributed by NM, 19-Jan-1997.)
statement:
sup2 $p |- ( ( A C_ RR /\ A =/= (/) /\ E. x e. RR A. y e. A ( y < x \/ y = x ) ) -> E. x e. RR ( A. y e. A -. x < y /\ A. y e. RR ( y < x -> E. z e. A y < z ) ) ) $.
$d A x y z $.
